ALIAS - Manage command shortcuts
=================================

Usage: alias              - List all aliases
       alias <name> <cmd> - Create an alias
       alias <name>       - Remove an alias
       alias reset        - Reset to defaults

Creates shortcuts for frequently used commands.

Examples:
  alias k attack      - 'k rat' becomes 'attack rat'
  alias h hp          - 'h' becomes 'hp'
  alias sc score      - 'sc' becomes 'score'
  alias               - List all current aliases
  alias k             - Remove the 'k' alias
  alias reset         - Reset all aliases to defaults

Default aliases include:
  n/s/e/w    - go north/south/east/west
  ne/nw/se/sw - diagonal movement
  u/d        - go up/down
  l          - look
  i/inv      - inventory

Aliases are saved when you quit and restored when you log in.

See also: help unalias, help aliases
